  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Kasztner transport is described more or less accurately in a number of pieces of literature.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But let me summarize it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Basically Dr.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Kasztner established a relationship with the Germans very soon after March 19.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the relationship was essentially based on Kasztner promising the Germans things that they wanted, and the Germans demanding things from Kasztner in exchange for Jewish lives.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The idea was, originally, that the Germans wanted 10,000 trucks.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they said that for 10,000 trucks they would trade 1 million Jews.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That was the statement made by Eichmann, who was the chief executioner of the Germans, and the head of the so-called Juden Kommando-- the Jewish Command of the Germans in Budapest.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And who, incidentally, had been in charge of evacuating and killing Jews for many years.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And you know about the Eichmann trial that took place in-- in Israel.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Eichmann essentially-- partly directly, partly indirectly-- Eichmann personally resented dealing with Jews.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So he usually did it through his associates, Becher or Krumey.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And Becher or Krumey, sometimes in the presence of Eichmann, proposed a deal of 10,000 trucks for 1 million Jews.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "In the meantime they deported and killed Jews, there were no million Jews available to-- and there's the long story that I don't want to go into because I don't really know the details of it.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But finally, what it amounted to was that-- that, as a gesture of goodwill, as a gesture of goodwill, Eichmann, with the full knowledge of Himmler-- Himmler was, whoever he was, you know-- offered to take in a transport of 600 Hungarian Jews, to take them into a protective camp.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And from there, via Spain, to deliver them to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
